    <worksheet name='Sales by Month'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run>Monthly Pharmaceutical Sales Trend</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
        <caption>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Business Question</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>How do pharmaceutical sales change throughout the year?</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Business Insight</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Sales are highest at the beginning of the year (January) and gradually decline until July, indicating a seasonal reduction in demand. Sales recover from August onward, reaching another peak around October before declining slightly at the end of the year. These trends can help inventory managers optimize stock levels, forecast demand, and plan promotional campaigns during slower months. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
      </layout-options>
