    <worksheet name='Total Sales'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> Total Sales by Drug </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
        <caption>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>This is the most important chart because it immediately answers:</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Which medicines contribute the most to the company’s sales?</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Æ </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>N02BE is the highest-selling drug category by a significant margin, making it the primary contributor to overall pharmaceutical sales. N05C records the lowest sales, indicating either niche usage or lower market demand. The company should prioritize inventory planning for high-performing products while investigating the factors affecting low-performing drugs.</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Æ </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
      </layout-options>
